items.title: Catering to Commuters at a Tijuana Border Crossing
items.summary: Every morning, tens of thousands commute from Tijuana, Mexico, into the United States for work, crawling for hours in traffic. A small industry of food vendors caters to the daily commuters.

items.title: Kuwait to Expel North Korean Ambassador, Other Diplomats
items.summary: Kuwait will expel North Korea's ambassador to the oil-rich country and four other diplomats, potentially limiting Pyongyang's ability to earn money for its nuclear program from laborers it sends to the Gulf.
